result.name: Hawker 18

reviews.text: Hawker 18 serves authentic Singaporean cuisine, including the signature Hainese Chicken. There is plenty of spice in the food, but they are happy to customize it for customers. The chairs are hard and could be a little more comfy, if there was some place to improve the dining experience. It is also hard to find the restaurant relative to the rest of the mall as it is hidden in the back.

It it a very interesting experience to try Singaporean style Hainese chicken rice. The taste is there and leaves me memories. I did try some soup and the spice is quite extreme, so I would not add too much pepper into it.

Shatin has been a good place to go either for shopping or eatery. This is another place to go for Laksa but this time an Indonesian fried rice was my choice. For under $100 in a decent restaurant is a must for lunch nowadays. A surplus of $4 for a special drink of Lorhonkwo with long Ngan. Moreover some credit card got 15% discount so check before payment.
Average food. Coconut chicken soup is just salty. Hainan chicken is tender but sauce and the soup that come with it are not special. Service is good though.
The flavor is there, but abit pricey.

reviews.text: Great place for shopping with lots of shops and restaurants. Phase III is currently under renovation but surprisingly, it provides clear directory to guide you to your destination. However, the mall is extremely busy, packed with tourists and locals. Recommend to go on weekday.

parkview restaurant is good. the all day breakfast is good and the price is reasonable. the restaurant provide good food and service. the pumpkin cream soup and English sausage is delicious but the bacon is too salty!!🤗🤔
Consists of high end fashion shops. You can find maja, Sandro, Zara, coach, longchamp those kind of shop. They also have a snoopy land right next to it. Good to kill time.
Very good mall with lots of good brands. Have very good promotional offers for luxury skin care brands. Purchased Estee lauder skin care set at more than half off the price
Big Shopping centre very good . Many BIg shop standby here. Transport famlier and convenient.

result.name: Hawker 18

reviews.text:
午餐由$78至百幾蚊不等
在沙田工作的人出示職員證有八折優惠

海南雞拼肉骨茶飯$115
雖然一次過可以有兩種滿足，但個湯唔夠熱同比較細碗有點遜色

招牌鱸魚完全唔脆，似預先炸好，二百蚊一味菜居然可以咁

雞油飯乾，懷疑係叮返熱

只有馬拉盞炒通菜好食

Hawker 18 serves authentic Singaporean cuisine, including the signature Hainese Chicken. There is plenty of spice in the food, but they are happy to customize it for customers. The chairs are hard and could be a little more comfy, if there was some place to improve the dining experience. It is also hard to find the restaurant relative to the rest of the mall as it is hidden in the back.
味道一般，兩份午餐埋單$192，食品味道和服務絕對唔值呢個價！

It it a very interesting experience to try Singaporean style Hainese chicken rice. The taste is there and leaves me memories. I did try some soup and the spice is quite extreme, so I would not add too much pepper into it.
